   D.L. Smith and L.P. Geraldo, ANL, March 1990.                  4125 1451
                                                                  4125 1451
  For complete documentation see Smith  and Geraldo [2].          4125 1451
                                                                  4125 1451
  Production of the isomer 93Nb-m by the (n,n') process is        4125 1451
routinely employed for neutron dosimetry applications. Isomer     4125 1451
is the first-excited state of the isotope 93Nb (30.82 keV         4125 1451
excitation energy). The reaction threshold energy is 31.15 keV.   4125 1451
The isotopic abundance of 93Nb in natural niobium is 100 %.       4125 1451
The half life of 93Nb-m is 16.1 years. The decay is entirely by   4125 1451
isomeric transition with nearly 100 % internal conversion.        4125 1451
                                                                  4125 1451
  The activity measurement is by observation of x-rays.           4125 1451
X-ray yields: 16.6 keV k-alpha (0.09238 per disintegration),      4125 1451
              18.6 kev k-beta (0.01802 per disintegration).       4125 1451
                                                                  4125 1451
  The evaluation is based on a least-squares adjustment procedure.4125 1451
Input information includes results from nuclear model             4125 1451
calculations and recent differential activation cross section     4125 1451
data from the literature. Uncertainties are derived from          4125 1451
experimental errors and the consideration of systematics.         4125 1451
